  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, how was the new project meeting?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "It was good, but a bit stressful. We discussed a lot of new features. I think we need to work hard to meet the deadline. By the way, I am watching a new Bollywood movie tonight."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Good to hear the meeting passed. Stress before deadlines is normal. What new feature feels heaviest?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The payment gateway integration is the biggest challenge. It needs to be very secure and fast. I am a bit worried about the timeline. Oh, and I invited some friends for the movie. Maybe we will have a good time."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it — secure and fast gateways are tricky. Did the team break it into smaller parts? The movie sounds fun — who’s coming?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yes, we split the work into smaller tasks. It helps a bit. I am not sure if we can finish on time, but we will try. The team is working hard. And for the movie, my friends Ravi and Aryan are coming. We often watch movies together. It's our weekend plan. Aryan knows a lot about Bollywood — he is a big fan."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Breaking tasks helps — good plan. Anymore fans in the group or just Ravi and Aryan?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Just them for now, but Ravi’s sister might join later. She loves Bollywood too — especially old Shah Rukh Khan movies. We might end up discussing them all night! 😄"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Old Shah Rukh Khan movies are a great choice — they spark endless talks. What’s your favorite SRK film?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite SRK film is definitely \"Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge.\" It's a classic! I watch it sometimes when I want to feel nostalgic. What about you, do you like it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Dilwale is a perfect pick — timeless and heartwarming. I love how it mixes tradition with romance. Have you seen any other old SRK films recently?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I saw \"Kuch Kuch Hota Hai\" a few days back. It's another classic — so many good memories attached to it. Sometimes I think old movies feel more real, you know? But I don't watch them too often, maybe once a month. How about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it — Kuch Kuch Hota Hai is rich with charm and nostalgia. Old movies do feel more real for many. What’s a modern Bollywood film you’ve liked lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, recently I liked \"Pathaan.\" It's an action movie with a lot of stunts and some good music. Shah Rukh Khan is back in his full star power. It was fun to watch with friends. Do you like action movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Action movies are exciting — especially with good stunts and music. Shah Rukh Khan brings a unique energy. Do you go for the action or the story more?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Both, honestly! The action keeps it entertaining, but I like when the story makes sense and has some emotional moments. Like in Pathaan, the mission was cool, but the character emotions made it better. What about you? Do you watch action movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You got it — balance is key. Action is just more fun with layers of emotion. I enjoy action when the stakes feel real. What's your favorite action hero?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Definitely Salman Khan for action — his movies are always full of energy and stunts. But Shah Rukh Khan is close second, especially in newer films. Thanks for the chat, Maya — I should get back to work. Talk to you soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Salman Khan's energy fits action perfectly — great pick. Talk soon, and take care with the work!\""
    }
  ],
